Origin and clean-room statement
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This is an ORIGINAL implementation of an embedded logic analyzer (ILA) core:
capture, trigger, run-length encoding, CSR, drain, and transport RTL plus the
Python host tooling and documentation in this repository were written from the
design document in docs/PLAN.md. No source code from any vendor ILA
(SignalTap, ChipScope/ILA, Reveal) or from LiteScope was copied, translated,
or adapted into this repository.

The repository layout, simulation harness conventions, and CI structure follow
the sibling "hyperram" project of the same organization (Apache-2.0).

The clock-domain-crossing FIFO follows the well-known publicly published
design technique described in Clifford E. Cummings' SNUG papers on
asynchronous FIFO design (gray-coded pointer comparison). The technique is
used as published engineering knowledge; no code was copied.

"SignalTap" is a trademark of Intel/Altera; "ChipScope" and "ILA" of
AMD/Xilinx; "Reveal" of Lattice Semiconductor. These names are used only to
describe the class of tool this project replaces; this project is independent
and unaffiliated.

